--------------------------------------------
1. make
2. make install


## install gsl (if dont have)
---------------------------------------------
1, download gsl

http://ftp.club.cc.cmu.edu/pub/gnu/gsl/

2 install

tar -zxvf gsl-1.9.tar.gz
cd gsl-xx

If you have root:
./configure
else:
./configure --prefix=/path/to/your/gsl/
make
make install

---------------------

If not, you can try setting the CPATH, LIBRARY_PATH and LD_LIBRARY_PATH variables:

export CPATH=/path/to/lib/gsl-2.2/include/
export LIBRARY_PATH=/path/to/lib/gsl-2.2/lib/
export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=/path/to/lib/gsl-2.2/lib/:$LD_LIBRARY_PATH
If it stil won't work, try creating, on your GSL folder, a symlink named lib64 to the folder lib:

cd /path/to/lib/gsl-2.2
ln -s lib lib64

